comment:
* Aggregates the information about request and response traffic for a
     * particular CronetEngine.

methods.name: public long getRequestHeaderSizeInBytes()
methods.comment: @return The total size of headers sent in bytes

methods.name: public long getRequestBodySizeInBytes()
methods.comment: @return The total size of request body sent, if any, in bytes

methods.name: public long getResponseHeaderSizeInBytes()
methods.comment: @return The total size of headers received in bytes

methods.name: public long getResponseBodySizeInBytes()
methods.comment: @return The total size of response body, if any, received in bytes

methods.name: public int getResponseStatusCode()
methods.comment: @return The response status code of the request

methods.name: public Duration getHeadersLatency()
methods.comment:
* The time it took from starting the request to receiving the full set of
         * response headers.
         *
         * @return The time to get response headers

methods.name: public Duration getTotalLatency()
methods.comment:
* The time it took from starting the request to receiving the entire
         * response.
         *
         * @return The time to get total response

methods.name: public String getNegotiatedProtocol()
methods.comment: @return The negotiated protocol used for the traffic

methods.name: public boolean wasConnectionMigrationAttempted()
methods.comment: @return True if the connection migration was attempted, else False

methods.name: public boolean didConnectionMigrationSucceed()
methods.comment: @return True if the connection migration was attempted and succeeded, else False
